Steps:

1. Download This Directory
2. run `npm install` (node version: v6.17.1 npm: 3.10.10)
3. mysql should be installed on local system
4. Login: mysql -uroot -p localdb12
5. Run: create database `forum`;
6. Run: use database `forum`;
7. Run: DEBUG=* node server.js
8. Once server comes up successfully. Open http://0.0.0.0:3000/documentation this on your Chrome.
9. You will find all APIs for test run. Can experiment

Thanks


Error Handling:

 ======> Promises then..catch functions Used for error handling

Asynchronous Functions Handling:

======> Hybrid of Async and Promises used

Data Definition Language:

=======> Sequelize Classes used for making relations and associations

========> Mysql ORM

=========> No Config files required, All Dynamic Params are stored in database only.

Kafka can be used for updating ancestor and descendant mappings.






